OP here, if waitlisted for the co-req it will NOT allow you to enroll in the course fyi.

If anyone else is in the same boat, I enrolled in Math 54 and then it allowed me into 100. Now to decide whether I can safely drop 54, or if I have to keep it blocking up space in my phase 1 units until I get off the EE waitlist....

Gonna email sishelp and update here if I get a response.

If a co-req is enforced by CalCentral (ie EE16a for Data100) does anyone know HOW enforcement is carried out? Will I be dropped from the course if I am on the waitlist for the co-req, rather than enrolled in the co-req?

If I am able to enroll in the course while waitlisted for the co-req, does that mean I have satisfied the co-req through CalCentral's eyes or will I be dropped later in the process (say, during waitlist processing, during the adjustment period, or at the onset of phase 2)?

Not sure if anyone knows enough about CalCentral's internal workings to answer, but worth a shot.

Thanks!
